    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Clean, Inspect, Measure, and Test
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Clean, Inspect, Measure, and Test</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields. Limit compressed
                        air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Measure Camshaft Lobe Lift</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If a complete engine overhaul is scheduled, camshaft wear can be accurately determined by
                        measuring with a micrometer after the camshaft is removed. See
                        <hotlnk document="eges3351_412.xml" xrefid="s1611">Measure Camshaft Lobes and Journals</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="s1611"/>. If this is not a complete engine overhaul, camshaft lobe lift can be
                        measured using the following procedure.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3350013355" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figh08/H08064.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Dial indicator with magnetic base</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para id="s1307" count="1">Mount a
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_341.xml" xrefid="t335001303">dial indicator set</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001303"/>
                    on the cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place dial indicator tip on top of push rod and rotate engine until push rod is at its
                    lowest point of travel (base circle), then "zero" indicator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft and bring push rod to its highest point of travel. Record
                    readings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat steps 2 and 3 for all twelve camshaft lobes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Compare readings to camshaft lobe lift
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_339.xml" xrefid="t335001301">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t335001301"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
